reviews.text: It‚Äôs a challenge to find the perfect cookie these days. And after my recent purchase of 4 cookies for $15.00 at Chip in Provo I am still looking for it. The cookies were hard and flavorless. It seemed like they put too much flour in each cookie. I couldn‚Äôt break one if I wanted to. I tried the OG chocolate chip and the Bischoff cookie and was terribly disappointed by them. Oh off I go to continue my perfect cookie quest.

Definitely A step above crumbl. The nicest changes that chip cookies are served warm (the way cookies should be) instead of those nasty chilled cookies from crumbl. Some of the toppings and options are very impressive and there's definitely a lot more customization.
Their cookies are soft and chewy, lots of great flavors, and they are always still great the next day. We love Chip!

So good! Cookies are flavorful and neatly put together. The taste YUMMY!
We ordered the Better than sex, tres Leche, and chocolate chip. We found a new cookie place.

Recommend 100%!! Crispy outer shell, soft center, delicious flavor with plenty of chocolate chips!! When I had an order delivered that was less than I had hoped, Chip immediately reached out and made things right. Great service + delicious cookies = loyal customer.
